";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:20:""Professor" Benjamin";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:3523:"<p>WordPress 4.5 release is getting very close. Currently, it is estimated to ship on April 12th. If you want to try out the latest version of WordPress you can download the <a href="https://wordpress.org/news/2016/03/wordpress-4-5-release-candidate/">4.5 release candidate</a>. This is also a good time to make sure that all your sites AND your clients sites have good backups.</p>
<h2 style="margin-top: 40px;">WordPress News</h2>
<ul>
<li>There have been concerns that <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/w3-total-cache/">W3 Total Cache</a> had been abandoned, but <a href="http://wptavern.com/frederick-townes-confirms-w3-total-cache-is-not-abandoned">Jeff Chandler was able to get in touch with Frederick Townes</a>, developer, and found that there are still plans for the plugin and it hasn&#8217;t been abandoned.</li>
<li>A very funny, though probably not safe for work (language), interview with the HBO cast of Silicon Valley try and guess what a tech company actually does. At around 1 minute 15 seconds they are <a href="http://wptavern.com/cast-of-silicon-valley-nails-the-meaning-of-automattic-on-the-first-try">asked about Automattic</a>.</li>
<li>Did you know the <a href="https://sourcecode.cio.gov/">US Government is working on adopting more open source software</a>and are looking for people to <a href="https://github.com/whitehouse/source-code-policy/issues">contribute to the discussion</a>. And since WordPress users deal with open source software everyday this is a great opportunity to contribute.</li>
<li>Business Insider has a great <a href="http://www.businessinsider.com/this-ceo-runs-a-billion-dollar-company-with-no-offices-or-email-2016-3">interview with Matt Mullenwe</a>g that talks about how Automattic has no offices of email.</li>
<li>Two excellent articles you don&#8217;t want to miss are the <a href="https://deliciousbrains.com/pressnomics4/">PressNomics 4 Highlights</a> and the <a href="https://wordimpress.com/freemium-ecosystem-part-1/">Freemium Plugin Ecosystem</a>.</li>
<li>If you are ready to take your PHP knowledge to the next level you need to read David Hayes&#8217;s article on <a href="http://wpshout.com/php-globals-variable-scope-wordpress/">PHP Globals and Variable Scope in WordPress</a>.</li>
</ul>
<h2 style="margin-top: 40px;">WordPress Plugins</h2>
<ul>
<li>If you&#8217;ve been looking for a new caching plugin you might want to check out <a href="http://wordpress.org/plugins/comet-cache">Comet Cache</a>, a plugin by the developers of S2Member.</li>
<li>Looking to create a custom experience for your clients using the WordPress customizer you might look at <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/kirki/">Kirki</a>, a toolkit for theme developers.</li>
<li>Integrate your WordPress posts into your Telegram feed with <a href="http://wordpress.org/plugins/telegram-for-wp">Telegram for WP</a>.</li>
</ul>
<p>I wanted to thank those of you who write me and let me know about plugins, news, tutorials and other pieces of content many of you create. I love adding that type of information to our<a href="https://ithemes.com/category/wordpress-weekly/">WordPress Weekly Recap posts</a>. You can also let me know about things you come across by emailing benjamin @ ithemes.com. Until next week  have a great day.</p>
