<h3>WordPress News</h3>
<ul>
<li>Are you looking for a way to take advantage of the latest<strong>Apple News</strong> format that was announced this week? You should head over to read this article at the <a href="http://thetechjournal.com/development/apple-news-format-wordpress.xhtml">Tech Journal on setting up Apple News with WordPress</a>.</li>
<li>Badoo published an excellent article looking at the <a href="https://techblog.badoo.com/blog/2016/03/14/how-badoo-saved-one-million-dollars-switching-to-php7"><strong>benefits that PHP7 provides</strong> for their server environment</a>. This could lead to HUGE benefits for WordPress sites.</li>
<li>I came across <strong>two quality freelancing articles</strong> this week. The first one emphasizes the <a href="https://codeable.io/power-of-no-freelancing">importance and power of saying &#8220;No&#8221;</a> in your business. And TorqueMag provides some very useful benefits that can be passed to clients if they need convincing when it comes to <a href="http://torquemag.io/2016/03/benefits-of-using-wordpress/">using WordPress as the platform of choice</a>.</li>
<li>Are you looking for a way to <strong>show your support for Apple</strong> in their case against the FBI? The <a href="https://savesecurity.org/">SaveSecurity site</a> is a way to stand with Apple in saying that encryption should be protected.</li>
</ul>
<h3>WordPress Plugins</h3>
<ul>
<li><a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/imagify/">Imagify Image Optimizer</a> is a plugin that should <strong>speed up your site</strong> by reducing all of the image sizes automatically.</li>
<li>A new<strong> <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/booking-ultra-pro/">&#8220;booking&#8221; plugin</a></strong> is now available that should help any business/job scheduling easier in WordPress.</li>
<li>If you want an easier way of using the WordPress Customizer to tweak the CSS look on different devices you will want to use this<strong><a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/advanced-css-editor/">Advanced CSS Editor</a></strong><a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/advanced-css-editor/"> plugin</a>.</li>
<li>Do you need a way to modify your site&#8217;s <strong>PHP settings</strong> from within the WordPress Dashboard? The <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/php-settings/">PHP Settings plugin</a> will create a local .ini settings file for your site.</li>
</ul>
<p>I wanted to thank those of you who write me and let me know about plugins, news, tutorials and other pieces of content many of you create. I love adding that type of information to our<a href="https://ithemes.com/category/wordpress-weekly/">WordPress Weekly Recap posts</a>. You can also let me know about things you come across by emailing benjamin @ ithemes.com. Until next week  have a great day.</p>
